{
  "texts": [
    "The disease composition spectrum of 11,428 patients was analyzed based on the \"primary diagnosis\" of discharge diagnosis.",
    "The most common cardiovascular issues were NSTEMI/UA Unstable Angina (24.3%), followed by Stable Angina Pectoris (14.8%) and STMI (7.4%).",
    "Other (Supplementary Table S3)",
    "We assessed the normality of the LLM's performance distribution using kurtosis, skewness, probability density curve, P-P diagram, and Q-Q diagram.",
    "(Supplementary Figure S1) Our analysis confirmed a normal distribution without significant outliers."
  ]
}